Wordcloud¶

Central Division(November Fiscal)¶

A visualisation method that displays how frequently words appear in a given body of text, by making the size of each word proportional to its frequency. All the words are then arranged in a cluster or cloud of words. Word clouds have recently become a staple of data visualization. They are especially popular when analyzing text.

In the Wordcloud-

1)Size - Represents occurence.

2)Color- Represents association with other frequently occuring words.

data['Customer Type'] = data['Phone tNPS'].apply(lambda x: "Detractor" if x>=0 and x<=6 else ("Passive" if x>=7 and x<=8 else "Promoter"))


dataPromoter=data[data['Customer Type']=='Promoter']
commentsPromoter=dataPromoter['Phone Reason for Score']

X_Promoter=x_promoter.str.lower()
